review_blob: Cherrywood on the nose, wonderful body and a subtle smokiness that lingers on the finish.
Quite nice. on draft at fourth street bar. slight sweetness, nice balance of alcohol. Great off keg. will give the bottle more time though.

Aroma of strawberry preserves. Flavor of slightly carmelized candied fruit. though, more complex than normal strwberry flavor. Not overly cloying on the finish. Had a very pleasant effervesance. Very good for a fruit beer.
This beer is one of the best Belgian wheat beers i have had.  A perfect summer beer.
My god this beer was good. Stole the show. Had it at BCTC. Well made with the perfect amount of oak. Whent back for a second pour on this one.  Just amazing.
I really do like this beer.  One of my two favorite styles. This beer improves with age. Ive had after a year and the flavors are really starting to get complex.
Had this beer on tap. Kinda boozy, really a little too sweet, but otherwise very very good. I really did enjoy it. Wish it was in bottles though, it could use a couple years of aging.
What didnt I like about this beer? Honestly loved it from the first whiff of the aroma all the way through its incredibly long finish. just amazing.

This beer caught me off gaurd. I was expecting something else when I tried this and was pleasantly surprised. I had from a 12 oz. bottle. poured beautifully. The aroma of carmel and malt was great. The beer was so smooth. Really liked it.
Light pink/white head, smelled of cherries. Nice and light, good balance of sweet and tart, with a dry finish.
MMM... This beer has a great malt presence, a little boozy, but in a good way. Carmal and a nice alcohol warming on the finish.
The spices in this beer were off the hook. I loved this beer.  I could drink it all the time. well, as a night cap really.
This beer is really very good. loved evey minute of it.  Though it can be hit and miss. make sure it is not too old.
Poured a very nice reddish brown with aromas of slight balsamic vinegar. Great malty body with nice sour finish. wished it had a little more sour character.
